data.value:
Example usage: {0} [[[/<key>=<value>] /<key>=<value>] ...]
<key>and <value>, where it is: UnattendedMode-Specifies whether to run wizard in unattended mode. Its values: true, false. Default value: false. If false or omitted, then the deployment wizard will be initialized by the rest of the passed values. If true, the deployment wizard will be launched in unattended mode.
DbProviderType-provider type in the database. Its values: {1}. default value: {2}
Settings common to all providers of DB:
ServerName-the name of the database server. Default value is undefined. ServerLogin-the user name for the administrative connection. Default value is undefined. ServerPassword-user password for the administrative connection. Default value is undefined. DatabaseName is the name of the database. Default value is undefined. DatabaseLogin-the user name to connect to the database. Default value is undefined. -DatabasePassword password to connect to the database. Default value is undefined. CreateNewDatabase is a sign of the need to create a new database. Its values: true, false. Default value: false. CreateNewDatabaseLogin-sign of the need to create a new database user. Its values: true, false. Default value: false. ConnectionString-storoka connect to the database. Default value is undefined. If the value is set, it will be used as the current configuration.
Settings for DB provider type {3}
ServerCredentialType-type administrative connection to a SQL Server database. Its values: {4}. default value: {5} DatabaseCredentialType-type of user connection to a SQL Server database. Its values: {6}. default value: {7}
Settings for DB provider type {8}
ServerDatabasePort-the port number that is used to connect to an Oracle database. Its values are: 0-65535. The default value is 1521. ServerDatabaseSID-SID of the Oracle database. Default value is undefined.
